<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 STILL IN CUSTODY AFTER BRAWL AT HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Los Angeles men remained in custody Sunday after a violent brawl that 
erupted during a birthday party at an Inglewood hotel Saturday night, leaving 
one party-goer dead. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested on suspicion of attempted murder were Michael Keith Williams, 20, his 
cousin, Marcus Williams, 21, and Delton Prescott, 24, Inglewood police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said guests at the Days Inn Park Plaza Hotel, located across the street 
from the Forum, became virtual hostages in their rooms after a rap music party 
ended with rampaging party-goers engaging in a running gun battle. 
</P>
<P>
Two men were wounded in a shoot-out that began in the ballroom and ended in the 
parking lot. In the panic that ensued, Roderick Williams, 22, of Los Angeles 
was killed when he was hit by a fleeing car, police said. The three men 
arrested are not suspects in the hit-and-run, police said, adding that they are 
still seeking the driver of the car. 
</P>
<P>
Prescott was in custody at the Los Angeles County Jail after treatment at a 
local hospital for a wound on his hand and the other two suspects were being 
held in Inglewood City Jail, Lt. David Garza said. Bail had not been set, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The disturbance began about 1:30 a.m. Saturday, when a fight broke out during 
the rap party that doubled as a birthday celebration for one of the guests, 
police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
