<HEADLINE>
<P>
LABOR DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today marks the celebration of Labor Day, set aside to recognize labor's 
contribution to the nation. 
</P>
<P>
Credit for the idea of Labor Day is given to Matthew Maguire, a New Jersey 
machinist, and Peter J. McGuire of New York, co- founder of a labor 
organization that eventually became the American Federation of Labor. After 
several states began observing the first Monday in September as Labor Day in 
the 1880s, Congress made the day a federal holiday in 1894. 
</P>
<P>
* Closed: All government offices, courts, banks, post offices, stock and 
commodity exchanges, libraries and many businesses. RTD buses will follow 
Sunday schedules. 
</P>
</TEXT>
