<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RESERVE OFFICER SUFFERS HEART ATTACK IN CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles Police Department reserve officer was in critical condition 
Sunday after suffering a heart attack during a foot chase in Pacoima. 
</P>
<P>
Officer Dennis Healy, 29, collapsed about 7:20 p.m. Saturday as he chased a man 
who appeared to be under the influence of drugs near Van Nuys Boulevard and 
Ilex Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Healy's partner, Officer Fred Torres, said in a report that Healy fell 
unconscious, suffering from "full cardiac arrest." 
</P>
<P>
Healy was taken by ambulance to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Torres and other officers later arrested Porfirio Castro, 18, on charges of 
resisting arrest. 
</P>
<P>
It was unknown if Healy had a history of heart trouble. 
</P>
</TEXT>
