<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GUNMAN KIDNAPS, RAPES TEEN-AGE GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old Van Nuys girl was kidnaped at gunpoint Sunday and raped, Los 
Angeles police reported. 
</P>
<P>
The girl told police a man forced her into his van at gunpoint near Sherman Way 
and Reseda Boulevard about 1 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
She said the man raped her and left her near Mureau and Calabasas roads in 
Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
She walked to a nearby school to call authorities. Sheriff's deputies found her 
at the school about 4 a.m. Sunday and contacted Los Angeles police. She was 
taken to a nearby hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The man -- possibly an Asian in his mid-20s, about 5 feet, 6 inches tall and 
weighing between 160 and 180 pounds -- drove a dark blue or gray van, said Los 
Angeles Police Sgt. William Weber. 
