<HEADLINE>
<P>
KIRK MCCASKILL NAMED ANGEL OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pitcher Kirk McCaskill, who defeated Nolan Ryan and the Texas Rangers on 
Tuesday with a complete-game shutout, has been named Angel of the Week by The 
Times' Orange County Edition. 
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old right-hander struck out four and allowed four hits in earning 
his 10th victory of the season. The shutout, his first since Aug. 20, 1989, 
lowered his earned-run average to 2.96, fifth-best in the American League. 
</P>
<P>
A check for $250 in McCaskill's name will be given to the Boys and Girls Clubs 
of Orange County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MCCASKILL, KIRK; BASEBALL PLAYERS; CALIFORNIA ANGELS (BASEBALL TEAM); HONORS 
</P>
